class Solution {
    public List<Integer> findDisappearedNumbers(int[] nums) {
        List<Integer> res=new ArrayList<>();
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            int index=Math.abs(nums[i])-1;
            if(nums[index]>0){
                nums[index]=-nums[index];
            }
        }
        for(int i=0;i<nums.length;i++){
            if(nums[i]>0) res.add(i+1);
        }
        return res;
    }
}

We traverse the array and use each value to mark its corresponding index as negative, indicating that number exists. After marking, we scan the array 
again and any index with a positive value represents a missing number. Those indices +1 are added to the result list.
